# Aim Brain Codex Master Doc

This is the phone-friendly single-file version of the Aim Brain / Codex project docs. Use this if downloading ZIP files is difficult on mobile.

Copy this file into your GitHub repo as `docs/AIM_BRAIN_MASTER_DOC.md`, or paste its contents into Codex before starting.

---

# 1. Product Identity

## Final app name

The app is named:

```text
Aim Brain
```

Older names like Aim Training Control Center / ATCC are historical only. New UI, docs, and code should use **Aim Brain**.

## One-sentence vision

```text
Aim Brain automatically imports aim-training data, stores clean raw runs locally, analyzes progress, and tells the user what to train next.
```

## What Aim Brain is

Aim Brain is:

- an automatic aim-training coach desktop app
- local-first
- automatic-import-first
- raw-run based
- coach-focused
- customizable
- low performance impact

It should help the user become a better aimer, not just collect statistics.

## What Aim Brain is not

Aim Brain is not:

- a spreadsheet replacement
- a manual score logger
- a Voltaic clone
- an EVXL clone
- only a benchmark browser
- only a leaderboard viewer
- only a stats dashboard
- a cloud-first social platform
- a noisy notification app

Tables, charts, and benchmark data can exist, but they support the coach system. They are not the product identity.

## Product promise

Aim Brain should make the user feel:

```text
My training is being captured.
My progress is being understood.
My weak points are clear.
My next session has a purpose.
```

