# 5. Aimlabs Import Research Questions

Before building the real parser, inspect real files or redacted samples.

## Must discover

1. Exact folder structure
2. Exact file names
3. Whether files are created automatically or only after export
4. Whether files are overwritten or appended
5. Whether data is JSON, CSV, SQLite, binary, or mixed
6. Whether it updates after every run, after closing Aimlabs, or only after clicking Download Data
7. Whether old runs are included or only recent/exported runs
8. Whether runs have unique IDs
9. Whether timestamps include timezone/milliseconds
10. Whether score and accuracy are numbers or strings
11. Whether overshoot/undershoot exists
12. Whether schema changes between exports

## Redaction rules for samples

Before committing sample files, remove or replace:

- username
- email
- account IDs
- Steam/Discord IDs
- exact local username
- full personal file paths
- IP addresses
- tokens
- access keys
- private profile links

Keep:

- field names
- structure
- fake/example values
- representative run rows
- timestamp format

Expected sample:

```text
samples/aimlabs/example_task_data.redacted.json
```

