# 7. Duplicate Detection

Duplicate runs are the same training attempt imported more than once.

This can happen when:

- user re-imports the same JSON
- app rescans the same folder
- Aimlabs rewrites/export files
- app restarts and scans old files
- two import methods see the same run

Compare:

- platform
- source-specific run ID if available
- scenario/task identifier
- normalized scenario name
- score
- timestamp
- duration
- accuracy
- source file hash
- source row hash

Duplicate confidence:

```text
exact_duplicate
probable_duplicate
possible_duplicate
not_duplicate
```

Exact duplicates can be skipped automatically. Uncertain duplicates go to review.

Do not silently delete raw runs.

---

# 8. Scenario Matching

Imported names may differ from canonical names.

States:

```text
matched
probably_matched
unmatched
needs_user_confirmation
```

When user confirms a match, save an alias so the app does not ask again.

Never blindly merge similar names if platform, version, or difficulty may differ.

Example variants:

```text
VT Air Angelic 4
Kovaak VT Air Angelic 4
VT Air Angelic 4 Easy
VT Air Angelic 4 - Aimlabs
```

