# 10. Category Coaching Notes

## Static Clicking

Trains:

- precision
- target acquisition
- stopping power
- click timing
- microcorrection

Weakness signs:

- overflicking
- shaky microcorrections
- clicking before stable
- slow target acquisition
- low first-shot accuracy

Suggestions:

- slow down enough to land on target
- focus on stop-before-click
- use smaller controlled movements
- avoid panic clicking

## Dynamic Clicking

Trains:

- moving target reads
- click timing under motion
- target prediction
- smooth approach

Weakness signs:

- chasing the target
- poor lead
- panic clicks
- late click timing
- inconsistent rhythm

Suggestions:

- track briefly before clicking
- prioritize timing over raw speed
- use easier moving target variants if needed

## Smooth Tracking

Trains:

- continuous control
- smoothness
- tension management
- matching velocity

Weakness signs:

- jitter
- falling behind target
- overcorrecting
- inconsistent pressure
- losing smoothness after direction changes

Suggestions:

- relax grip
- match target velocity
- use longer controlled runs
- avoid overcorrecting

## Reactive Tracking

Trains:

- direction-change reading
- braking
- reaction
- correction speed

Weakness signs:

- late reactions
- overshooting direction changes
- losing target after dodge
- guessing direction too early

Suggestions:

- focus on staying centered
- react to changes, do not wildly predict
- choose difficulty where control remains possible

## Speed Switching

Trains:

- fast target acquisition
- transition speed
- pathing
- rhythm

Weakness signs:

- hesitation
- bad pathing
- overshooting transitions
- slow confirmation

Suggestions:

- clean target order
- reduce wasted pathing
- gradually raise speed
- maintain confirmation before click

## Evasive Switching

Trains:

- switching plus moving/evasive target control
- mixed tracking and clicking
- visual read under complexity

Weakness signs:

- panic
- losing target during transition
- poor first confirmation
- overflicking into moving targets

Suggestions:

- slow down first shot
- confirm target before committing
- strengthen dynamic clicking and reactive tracking base

