# 11. Readiness Score

Readiness should not be only PB-based.

Components:

- PB readiness
- last-10 average readiness
- consistency readiness
- category balance
- recent activity/freshness
- confidence score

Example:

```text
Master Readiness: 74%
PB Readiness: 82%
Consistency Readiness: 68%
Weakest blocker: Reactive Tracking
Main issue: last-10 average is below target
```

---

# 12. Session Summary System

Core rule:

```text
Save every run.
Analyze silently.
Summarize only when useful.
Show summaries only at the user's chosen feedback level.
```

## Summary increments

### Every run

Save silently.

Allowed small events:

- new PB popup if enabled
- import error
- suspicious duplicate
- unknown scenario
- review needed

### Every 5-10 runs

Update block stats quietly.

### Scenario block summary

Triggers:

- 5+ runs on same scenario
- or 8-12 minutes on same scenario
- or user switches scenario
- or end of session

Example:

```text
VT Air Angelic 4 block summary

Runs: 8
Best: 842
Average: 811
Last-5 average: 824
PB: yes, +2.8%

Coach note:
Your best score improved, but the average moved only slightly.
Good peak, not stable yet.
```

### Category summary

Triggers:

- 15-30 minutes in one category
- or 2+ scenarios from same category
- or end of session

### Full session summary

Default session detection:

- session starts when first run is imported
- session ends after 15-20 minutes with no new runs
- or when Aimlabs/KovaaK's closes if detectable
- or when user presses End Session

Example:

```text
Session imported: 42 runs

Time trained: 54 minutes
Categories trained: 3
New PBs: 4
Best category: Reactive Tracking
Weakest category today: Dynamic Clicking
Most improved scenario: VT Air Angelic 4
Consistency: 78%
Fatigue trend: mild drop near the end

Coach note:
You improved your peaks today, but your last-10 averages were unstable.
Next session should focus on controlled repeatability, not PB chasing.
```

### Daily summary

Combines multiple sessions in one calendar day.

### Weekly coach report

Default trigger:

- every 7 days
- or after at least 3 training days
- user configurable

### Monthly review

Longer-term progress review.

