# 17. Performance Requirements

Aim Brain must not hurt aim-training performance.

## Idle

- near-zero CPU
- modest RAM usage
- no constant heavy loops
- no unnecessary network activity

## While training

- no heavy chart rendering
- no expensive analytics loops
- no noisy popups unless enabled
- file watcher should be debounced
- imports can wait until run/session ends if needed

## After training

- import new runs
- calculate summaries
- update dashboard
- generate coach notes

## Gaming Mode / Low-Impact Mode

Gaming Mode should:

- silence popups
- reduce background work
- delay heavy summaries
- avoid chart updates during active training
- keep only essential file watching
- allow import after session

Possible modes:

- Normal
- Low Impact
- Import After Session Only
- Manual Scan Only

